<ValidityStateBadInput>
<summary>
The read-only <strong><c>badInput</c></strong> property of a <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ValidityState">ValidityState</see> object indicates if the user has provided input that the browser is unable to convert. For example, if you have a number input element whose content is a string.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation">Guide: Constraint validation</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Form_validation">Tutorial: Form data validation</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ValidityState/badInput"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A boolean.</value>
</ValidityStateBadInput>
